Your points are well thought out and very accurate. I accept the admonishment willingly. Yes, getting involved in such online romances is not morally upright. I along with many others who are in RL relationships are guilty of this. We look at it innitially as just a game, and the romance as make-believe. Eventually real feelings develop and the ante is raised. If you take a look at every couple sharing a last surname in EQ, I guarentee you will find the majority of them are married in RL to somebody other than their EQ marraige partner.<br>
<br>
As to my unleashing of information about Merianne, that was a loss of temper resulting from her deliberate aims at trying to simply cause problems for the characters on this account. If it were simply warning others to beware of getting involved romantically with chars on this account, my response would have been...as it was...measured. She went the added length of posting on the guild board of my friend Eldarious' guild. Her objectives here were only to inflict harm and cause trouble, not just issue her warning. Since Eldarious has no plans or aims at getting involved with females online, I don't think warning females to avoid him would really be any trouble for him. She took my post and applied it to him with the intent of trying to make Seventh Ward be offended by him. It was a malicious cheap shot that was not called for simply because I asked Merianne if we could just be friends, and end our online romantic involvement.<br>
<br>
Countess Consuela,<br>
If you read my post more carefully, you would see that the relationship I spoke of in it was not Merianne but I was speaking of my first online relationship. There were many... including the one with you, I assume... that happened between that one and Merianne. And why do you always replace &quot;ended the relationship&quot; with the term &quot;hurt me/her/them&quot;? You always say &quot;Truehart hurt me ... Truehart hurt them... Truehart hurt her&quot; when the truth is, there was a reason my ending the relationship hurt you. That reason was that you did not want it to end. Otherwise, it would not have hurt you. So the truth is, I was a good partner... fun to be with, and I met your emotional needs at that time. The only thing that I did to &quot;Hurt You&quot; was to bring the relationship to an end. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showMessage?topicID=82.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showMessage?topicID=110.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.threadControl?topicID=229.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=229.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=229.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub28.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacin